  "body": "# Problem \r\n\r\nCurrently we are using a function call to determine what action to take depending on the platform. This leads to unnecessary code execution and dead code on each platform, as well as unnecessary complex code organization.\r\nFor instance notification code is mostly unusable by desktop and desktop would use a completely different implementation.\r\nFinally we want to be able to test different expectations for different platforms. If for a given event iOS is expected to do X and Android X+Y, this should be testable. Therefore we should consider passing platform in the cofx.\r\n \r\n# Solution\r\n\r\nThere is two different solutions here for the different use cases:\r\n- for small differences in code execution, we can use :closure-defines compiler options. The result is that if we have a when statement for instant for platform/iOS?, closure compiler will remove it on Android and desktop\r\n- for bigger differences such as notifications, we should have different source directories for desktop/mobile so that code that will not work on desktop/mobile is simply not compiled.",
